          "settings": {
            "heading": "A Craft with Deep Roots",
            "highlight_font": "body",
            "seo_heading": "h2",
            "size": "h2",
            "content": "<p>Hand block printing is a long-standing textile tradition in India, passed down through generations of skilled makers. It is a careful, hands-on process that values patience, precision, and a strong understanding of pattern, color, and cloth.</p><p>Each design begins with a carved wooden block. The block is dipped in dye and pressed onto fabric by hand, again and again, until the pattern comes together. That rhythm is what gives block print its character: you can see the work of the hand in every repeat.</p><p>Because each piece is printed manually, no two are exactly alike. Those slight variations are part of the beauty. They remind us that handmade textiles bring warmth, individuality, and a sense of heritage that machine-made fabric cannot quite replicate.</p>"
          }
        }
