        "text_nbxhTC": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p><strong>1. Carving the block:</strong> The design is first carved into wood by hand, with each block made to print a specific part of the pattern.</p><p><strong>2. Preparing the color:</strong> Dyes are mixed and tested so the print lands clearly and keeps its depth on cotton.</p><p><strong>3. Printing by hand:</strong> The block is pressed onto the fabric one repeat at a time, with careful alignment and a steady rhythm.</p><p><strong>4. Washing and finishing:</strong> Once printed, the fabric is set, washed, and finished so it feels soft and ready for everyday use.</p>"
